section.def:
contain
                (含有), in relation to a food animal, means to be
            present in any tissue, body fluid or milk of the food animal;

fodder
                (飼料) means any substance commonly used for the
            food of food animals;

lairage
                (牲口欄) means a part of a slaughterhouse which is
            used for the confinement of food animals;

Public
                Analyst
                (政府分析員) means the Government Chemist;

slaughterhouse
                (屠房) has the meaning assigned to it by
                section 2(1) of the Public Health and Municipal Services Ordinance (Cap. 132);

tissue
                (組織) includes meat, offal, hair and any part of a
            food animal;

td.p:
Each animal
                                must carry a tag in its ear measuring not less than 3 cm by 6 cm and
                                printed with at least 6 alphanumeric characters;

